
===================================
📌 1. Finglish Version (Persian Latin Script)
===================================

📖 **Tashrih:**
    Dastoor `colrm` baraye hazf kardan (remove) sotoon-ha (columns) az voroodi (input) estefade mishavad. Shoma mitavanid yek range az sotoon-ha ra baraye hazf moshakhas konid. Agar shoma faghat yek adad bedahid, `colrm` hameye sotoon-ha az aan adad be baad ra hazf mikonad.

⚙️ **Gozine-ha:**
    🔹 `colrm start` --> 🗑️ Hazf hameye sotoon-ha az sotoon `start` ta akhar khat.
    🔹 `colrm start stop` --> ✂️ Hazf sotoon-ha az sotoon `start` ta sotoon `stop`.

🛠 **Mesal-ha:**

    $ echo "Hello World" | colrm 6
    Hello

    🔹 In mesal, hameye characters az sotoon 6 (W) be baad hazf mishavand.

    $ echo "1234567890" | colrm 3 7
    127890

    🔹 In mesal, characters az sotoon 3 ta 7 hazf mishavand.

✅ **Mesal sade:**

    $ echo "abcdefgh" | colrm 4
    abc

    🔹 Sotoon-ha az 4 be baad hazf shodeh va natijeh namayesh dadeh mishavad.

===================================
📌 2. English Version
===================================

📖 **Description:**
    The `colrm` command is used to remove columns from input. You can specify a range of columns to remove. If you only provide one number, `colrm` removes all columns from that number onwards.

⚙️ **Options:**
    🔹 `colrm start` --> 🗑️ Remove all columns from column `start` to the end of the line.
    🔹 `colrm start stop` --> ✂️ Remove columns from column `start` to column `stop`.

🛠 **Examples:**

    $ echo "Hello World" | colrm 6
    Hello

    🔹 In this example, all characters from column 6 (W) onwards are removed.

    $ echo "1234567890" | colrm 3 7
    127890

    🔹 In this example, characters from column 3 to 7 are removed.

✅ **Simple Example:**

    $ echo "abcdefgh" | colrm 4
    abc

    🔹 Columns from 4 onwards are removed, and the result is displayed.
